Subject: FSAC SystemIndexOutofRange
Description: FSAC SystemIndexOutofRange error when running FSAC scans.
DevOps_Steps_to_Reproduce__c: FSAC job out of range occurs when running FSAC scan job.
What_We_Know__c:
IndexOutOfRange exception is being thrown and the FSAA scan seems to end abruptly with no errors. I suspect a resource error as we did see other scans and tasks such as the AIC struggling to start or run while other jobs were running. Upon stopping these jobs we were able to run other jobs successfully.

--------
02/03/2025
--------

Ran Tay's suggested plan. Scans seem to be working but previously they failed after multiple runs so we are waiting before we determine the issue is fixed.

Uninstalled the NEA console server.
Rebooted the console server.
Reinstalled to a new directory.
Ran the upgrade mode after reinstall.
Enabled debug logging.
Started FSAA scans.
Next_Steps__c: On hold for 00435344, issues my be linked.
Solution_Comment__c:
Symptom
FSAC scan returns SystemIndexOutofRange.


Resolution
Clearing T2 database and rescanning allowed the scan to run as expected.
